 f_k(x) = \frac{1}{k(1+kx)},\qquad 0\leq x<\infty, 
 \sum\limits_{n=1}^\infty f_k(x). 
 f(x)  = \sum\limits_{n=1}^\infty f_k(x) 
(0,\infty)
\delta > 0
\lvert x - x0\rvert < \delta
\lvert f(x+\delta) -f(x)\rvert < \epsilon
\delta < \frac{\epsilon\cdot x^2}{\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n^2}}
A=(0,\infty)
